<TITLE> Habibur Rahman to be acting ACC chief: official </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 7 (bdnews24.com)Commissioner Habibur Rahman has been appointed acting chief of the Anticorruption Commission, an ACC official said Tuesday. A Cabinet Division order approved by the president has been sent to the ACC headquarters, said the official, asking not to be named as he was not authorised to speak to the media. "An order to appoint commissioner Habibur Rahman as the temporary chairman came to the ACC [Tuesday noon]," he told bdnews24.com ACC chief Hasan Mashhud Chowdhury stepped down Thursday, saying little about the reason for his resignation. "I think you all know the situation now prevailing; there's no need for me explain it," the former army chief told the press, before leaving the ACC headquarters. bdnew
